title: Distinct Subsequences
content: Given two strings and , return the number of distinct subsequences of which equals . A string's subsequence is a new string formed from the original string by deleting some (can be none) of the characters without disturbing the relative positions of the remaining characters. (i.e., is a subsequence of while is not). It's guaranteed the answer fits on a 32-bit signed integer. and consist of English letters.
